      <div xml:id="NA51-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">iḵtu āṟṟatētam añci vēṟuppaṭṭāḷ veṟiyāṭaluṟṟaviṭattu ciṟaippuṟamākac colliyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what is said, afraid suffering that is unbearable, by her who was changed when the Veṟi dance took place while [HE] was behind the fence.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA51">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            yāṅkuccey vāṅko ṟōḻi yōṅkukaḻaik</l>
<l>            kāmpuṭai viṭarakañ cilampap pāmpuṭaṉ</l>
<l>            ṟōṅkuvarai miḷira vāṭṭi vīṅkucelaṟ</l>
<l>            kaṭuṅkura lēṟoṭu kaṉaituḷi talaiip</l>
<l>            peyalā ṉātē vāṉam peyaloṭu </l>
<l>            miṉṉunimirn taṉṉa vēlaṉ vanteṉap</l>
<l>            piṉṉuviṭu mucci yaḷippā ṉātē</l>
<l>            peruntaṇ kuḷavi kuḻaitta pāvaṭi</l>
<l>            yiruñcē ṟāṭiya nutala kolkaḷiṟu</l>
<l>            pētai yāciṉi yocitta </l>
<l>            vītā vēṅkaiya malaikiḻa vōṟkē.</l>
            </lg>
       <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>What can we do, friend?</l>
<l rend="indent">Offering intense drops with harsh-voiced [thunder-]strokes,</l>
<l rend="indent">a swelling movement, shaking, so that they overturn,</l>
<l rend="indent">the high mountains [and] upsetting snakes,</l>
<l>while high the bamboos, shafts snapping, resound inside caves,</l>
<l>rain [is] unending.</l>
<l rend="indent3">With the sky raining,</l>
<l rend="indent3">since the priest came, [spear] extended like a flashing,</l>
<l rend="indent2">care for [my hair] tuft, which lets go the braids, [is] unending.</l>
<l>– about the lord from the mountain of flower-spreading Vēṅkai trees,</l>
<l rend="indent">where the deadly elephant bull with broad feet, that mashed</l>
<l rend="indent">the big cool wild jasmine [and] a forehead that played in the dark</l>
<l rend="indent">mud, has broken(?)<note place="foot">The form <term xml:lang="ta">ocitta</term> is difficult to explain here. The usual form to be expected in this position and function is the pey. <term xml:lang="ta">ocittum</term>.</note> the innocent(?)<note place="foot">How to understand <term xml:lang="ta">pētai</term> here? The point might be that the tree had given no offence to the attacking elephant bull. T.V.G. reads an elliptical causal clause: the elephant shakes the tree 'out of foolishness'.</note> breadfruit tree.</l>
        </lg>
